          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #20\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#313\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cupy_processing/canvas.py:44`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cupy_processing/canvas.py:55`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cv2_processing/canvas.py:61`\n\nCPU allocates a channel-aware canvas. GPU always allocates a 2-D canvas and assigns the input into it.\n\nImpact:\n\n- 3-channel CuPy images fail or require special backend handling.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Mirror CPU canvas shape handling for 3-D input, or explicitly reject non-2-D input.\n- Add CPU/GPU parity tests for color inputs.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-25T02:48:44Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in commit 2797f63. GPU canvas now mirrors CPU channel-aware allocation: 2-D input -> 2-D canvas, 3-D (colour) input -> 3-channel canvas. Three parity tests added.",
                "createdAt": "2026-05-25T02:48:44Z",
                "id": "IC_kwDOONYVBs8AAAABDhN84w",
                "reactions": {
                  "nodes": []
                },
